  "note": "<div style=\"text-align:left\"><b>Flip</b>, reverses a string of <i>a</i>s and <i>b</i>s (e.g. <i>bbaaa</i> → <i>aaabb</i>).<br><br>\n<b>How it works:</b> It places a <i>#</i> to mark the start and a <i>$</i> to mark the end of the string, then repeatedly takes the rightmost character, erases it, and writes it to the left of <i>#</i>.<br><br>\n<b>States:</b>\n<ul>\n  <li><b>S0</b>  : Reads the first <i>a</i> or <i>b</i> and moves left to S1.</li>\n  <li><b>S1</b>  : Reads the blank to the left of the string, writes <i>#</i> to mark the start, then moves right to S2.</li>\n  <li><b>S2</b>  :  Loops right over <i>a</i>s and <i>b</i>s; on reading a blank, writes <i>$</i> and moves left back onto the string, going to S3.</li>\n  <li><b>S3</b>  : Rewinds right-to-left to find the <i>#</i>, then moves to S4.</li>\n  <li><b>S4</b>  : Reads the next character right of <i>#</i>: if <i>a</i>, erases it and goes to S5; if <i>b</i>, erases it and goes to S6; if <i>$</i>, erases it and accepts (S10).</li>\n  <li><b>S5 / S6</b>  : Carrying a character leftward. S5 carries an <i>a</i>, S6 carries a <i>b</i>. Each moves left over blanks until hitting <i>#</i>, then continues to S7 or S8.</li>\n  <li><b>S7 / S8</b>  : Moves left over any <i>a</i>s and <i>b</i>s to find the leftmost blank, writes <i>a</i> (S7) or <i>b</i> (S8), then moves right back to S9.</li>\n  <li><b>S9</b>  : Moves right over <i>#</i> back to the dispatch position S4 to process the next character.</li>\n  <li><b>S10</b> : Accept. The reversed string is on the left of where <i>#</i> was.</li>\n</ul></div>",
  "defaultInput": "bbaaa"
}